From 0000000000000000000000000000000000000000 Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: Carbonyl Maintainers <carbonyl@integrolabs.net>
Date: Wed, 21 May 2026 13:00:00 +0000
Subject: [PATCH 27/27] carbonyl: install --dump-text handler on
 OnBrowserStart's WebContents

Wires `carbonyl::DumpTextHandler::StartFor()` into the headless shell's
`OnBrowserStart()`, right after the initial `HeadlessWebContents` is
built. Pre-existing carbonyl patch 0009 already removed the upstream
`HeadlessCommandHandler::ProcessCommands(...)` invocation from this
function; this patch re-establishes a carbonyl-owned command-handler
hook at the same site.

The handler is no-op unless `--dump-text` is present on the process
command line (parsed by the Rust CLI at `src/cli/cli.rs`, but visible
to `base::CommandLine::ForCurrentProcess()` here for free because the
user typed it on argv). When active, it observes the WebContents
through the content layer's `ExecuteJavaScriptInIsolatedWorld` API and
writes the extracted page text to stdout, then triggers chromium's
orderly shutdown via `HeadlessBrowserImpl::ShutdownWithExitCode()`
(per #93 — replaces the earlier `std::_Exit` path).

The handler deliberately does not use the upstream
`HeadlessCommandHandler` because that path depends on
`headless_enable_commands = true`, which is incompatible with
carbonyl's `headless_use_embedded_resources = true` build (see
`BUILD.gn` assert in `chromium/src/headless/BUILD.gn`).

The new `//carbonyl/src/browser:dump_text` GN component is kept
separate from `:bridge` because `:bridge` sits below skia in the dep
graph; pulling `//content/public/browser` into it would introduce a
cycle. The new component depends on `:bridge`'s siblings (`//base`,
`//content/public/browser`, and `//headless:headless_browser` for the
`HeadlessBrowserImpl` shutdown call) and is pulled in by
`headless_shell` only.

See `chromium/src/carbonyl/src/browser/dump_text_handler.{cc,h}` for
the handler implementation and `docs/runtime-modes.md` Mode 4 for the
operator-facing documentation.

Refs: roctinam/carbonyl#88
Refs: roctinam/carbonyl#93
Refs: roctinam/carbonyl#4
Refs: roctinam/carbonyl#5
---
 headless/BUILD.gn              |  1 +
 headless/app/headless_shell.cc | 13 +++++++++++++
 2 files changed, 14 insertions(+)

diff --git a/headless/BUILD.gn b/headless/BUILD.gn
index 28d25d86087a9..4691cdc61cbac 100644
--- a/headless/BUILD.gn
+++ b/headless/BUILD.gn
@@ -946,6 +946,7 @@ executable("headless_shell") {

   deps = [
     ":headless_shell_lib",
+    "//carbonyl/src/browser:dump_text",
     "//carbonyl/src/browser:renderer",
     "//build:branding_buildflags",
     "//components/os_crypt/common:switches",
diff --git a/headless/app/headless_shell.cc b/headless/app/headless_shell.cc
index 2446f07b906c2..f7ac18c3eff01 100644
--- a/headless/app/headless_shell.cc
+++ b/headless/app/headless_shell.cc
@@ -4,6 +4,7 @@

 #include "headless/public/headless_shell.h"

+#include "carbonyl/src/browser/dump_text_handler.h"
 #include "carbonyl/src/browser/renderer.h"

 #include <memory>
@@ -149,6 +150,18 @@ void HeadlessShell::OnBrowserStart(HeadlessBrowser* browser) {
     LOG(ERROR) << "Navigation to " << target_url << " failed.";
     ShutdownSoon();
   }
+
+  // Carbonyl issue #88: install the --dump-text observer on the freshly
+  // built WebContents. No-op unless --carbonyl-dump-text is on the
+  // command line (set by the Rust CLI when the user passed --dump-text).
+  if (web_contents && carbonyl::DumpTextHandler::IsRequested()) {
+    // Passing `browser` along enables the ordered-shutdown path in
+    // DumpTextHandler::EmitAndExit (per #93). The handler downcasts to
+    // HeadlessBrowserImpl to call ShutdownWithExitCode.
+    carbonyl::DumpTextHandler::StartFor(
+        HeadlessWebContentsImpl::From(web_contents)->web_contents(),
+        browser);
+  }
 }

 #if defined(HEADLESS_ENABLE_COMMANDS)
--
2.43.0
